<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1667922-in-the-novel-bella-is-very-clearly">In the novel Bella is very clearly described as having blonde hair, but the cover art shows a brunette. Do you think the cover artist was just an idiot who couldn&#39;t be bothered to actually learn what the character is supposed to look like?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1667922'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F10081055-beauty-and-the-werewolf">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1667922-in-the-novel-bella-is-very-clearly">one year ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1667922-in-the-novel-bella-is-very-clearly">Add your answer</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/12466918-christopher-roxby"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1347065895i/12466918._UY100_CR9,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/12466918-christopher-roxby">Christopher Roxby</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I wondered that too, until I had a conversation (briefly) with author David Morell (First Blood). <br/>Turns out that in most cases, the artist is given on<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I wondered that too, until I had a conversation (briefly) with author David Morell (First Blood). <br />Turns out that in most cases, the artist is given only a vague description of what the publisher wants for the cover, and it often has nothing whatever to do with the story inside. Most times the author has no say in it. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

