<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1058147-my-library-copy-hardbound-has-5-blank">My library copy, hardbound, has 5 blank pages at the end. Why? If it weren&#39;t a library book, I would use those pages to write or create art about the book. Is this intentional?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1058147'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F10081055-beauty-and-the-werewolf">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1058147-my-library-copy-hardbound-has-5-blank">4 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1058147-my-library-copy-hardbound-has-5-blank">Add your answer</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/43727848-zo-sumra"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1443042627i/43727848._UX100_CR0,25,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/43727848-zo-sumra">Zoë Sumra</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Hardbound books are all printed in multiples of either 16 or 24 pages - due to the workings of the printing press. If the book text doesn&apos;t run to a m<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Hardbound books are all printed in multiples of either 16 or 24 pages - due to the workings of the printing press. If the book text doesn't run to a multiple of 16 or 24 pages, the book will end up with blank pages at the back.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

