<div id="review_982011224" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/982011224" />
    <a title="Dawn Livingston" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/28140212-dawn-livingston"><img alt="Dawn Livingston" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1485635007p2/28140212.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/982011224?book_show_action=true">Aug 13, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Dawn Livingston" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Dawn Livingston" href="/user/show/28140212-dawn-livingston">Dawn Livingston</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/28140212-dawn-livingston?shelf=just-not-into-it-gave-up">just-not-into-it-gave-up</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer982011224" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3392417483053538601">I gave up on this story pretty quickly. Just a combination of Beauty and the Beast and Little Red Riding Hood. Nothing special. It also seemed strangely young adultish rather than adult material. Was that intentional?<br/><br/>(borrowed from another reviewer who said it better than I could) I like a practically minded, strong willed girl capable of getting things done as much as the next person. But you don&apos;t have to look down on everyone else as lesser than thou, nor be perfect at everything, nor bask in</span>
  <span id="freeText3392417483053538601" style="display:none">I gave up on this story pretty quickly. Just a combination of Beauty and the Beast and Little Red Riding Hood. Nothing special. It also seemed strangely young adultish rather than adult material. Was that intentional?<br /><br />(borrowed from another reviewer who said it better than I could) I like a practically minded, strong willed girl capable of getting things done as much as the next person. But you don't have to look down on everyone else as lesser than thou, nor be perfect at everything, nor bask in how everyone adores you even though you are kind of condescending manipulator who can't take any responsibility for anything. She's that one girl that I can never stand, the one who assumes that just because she was born with brains and some beauty, she's perfect. She knows best all the time. She is never wrong about anything.<br /><br />If you like Lackey, her Five Hundred Kingdoms series which I do not or think a story that mixes Little Red Riding Hood and Beauty and the Beast sounds interesting, then this book is for you.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3392417483053538601" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

